latestIgtvVideos.title: Fair Disclaimer: Your Shivangi Didi is actually upset today
latestIgtvVideos.caption: For the longest time I’ve been making videos around fashion and design. I’ve been creating authentic detailed videos which add value to your lives and help you start your journey in design. Today, I am sad. Really sad. :) Not because I’ve encountered haters BUT because I’ve encountered those who’ve been copying my content, my format of videos, my titles and subject tag lines to actually have the audacity to reach out to me and tell me that I’ve copied (OR I AM COPYING THEIR CONTENT) LOL. THE VIDEO TAKES YOUR THROUGH MAILS AND CONVERSATIONS FROM TWO YEARS BACK ON THIS TOPIC AND ALSO AS FRESH AS 14 WEEKS BACK. RIGHT BEFORE THE LOCKDOWN. I couldn’t execute it because my Bauji was sick and I was moving my studio. BUT BUT BUT People who’ve been copying my content on YouTube, it must have been so easy for them to find me here, see the stories or the highlights and copy the same idea. Sure you posted it first, but people who follow me know I initiated the idea here and after three months of that you “started” it. :) And yet they have the audacity to reach out to me and misguide other kids :) People know who’s original. But this is just to shut those down who needed an answer. :) Love.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Cozy Little Corner 💕
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Cannot find a space which motivates you or makes you feel happy? Bored of being stuck at home? Maybe your space just needs a little makeover. I was going through a similar phase when I decided to take things in my own hands and spruce up my space a little to create a small cozy corner. This is my favourite place in my room now AND I did it by just adding elements which were already in my room so it’s zero investment! Woohoo! (: Try a low seating and tag me in your stories if this inspired you even a little! Much love. 
PS: Sorry about the quality. Worked on a new app, hence the resolution compromise 🙈 #HomeDecor #cozy #roomdecor #diy #cozycorner #lbb #wfh @lbb.mumbai

latestPosts.caption:
“They told me to follow the rules.
But I was busy designing my own.”

I wasn’t born with a blueprint.
No godfather in the industry.
No safety net if I failed. 
Just big dreams… 

and the courage to start.

I’ve failed. 
I’ve pivoted. 
I’ve rebuilt.
And I’ve learned — you don’t find your path…
You design it.

🎤 “Design Your Life”: Out now on YouTube

#designerdidi #designershala #tedxspeaker #tedx #tedtalk #designyourlife #yourdreamfashionlife #manifest #manifestyourdreams #rebel #rebelwithacause

For the first time in a decade, I’ve slowed down.

Pregnancy has humbled me in ways I never anticipated.
I’ve spent the last ten years in go-getter mode- chasing dreams, hitting milestones, checking off bucket list goals like there’s no tomorrow.

But these past few months?
Life has brought me to a gentle pause.
My pace has dropped to 0.25x of what it used to be- and yet, I’ve never felt more present.

It’s not that I’ve become less productive.
If anything, I’ve become more intentional.
Every hour I spend working, resting, or just being… feels more aligned with what truly matters.

There’s a quiet kind of power in slowing down.
It teaches you to listen. To prioritize. To let go of the noise.

To all the mothers out there—balancing 9-5 jobs, running ventures, raising babies (and themselves)…
I see you.
I honor you.
You are doing more than enough.

#PregnancyJourney #WorkingMoms #LeadershipInMotherhood #MindfulLiving #WomenEntrepreneurs #designyourlife

latestPosts.caption:
I manifested this.

Last year, I was walking through the halls of NIFT Mumbai as a jury member- nostalgic, wide-eyed, remembering the version of me who once studied there.

And in that moment, I had a thought: What if I came back? Not just for a jury or a one-off class. But for real.

What if I stayed, showed up week after week, and gave back in a way I had always dreamt of?

For the first time in a decade, I was going to be in Mumbai for six uninterrupted months. No travel, no hopping cities. It felt like the right time to give back meaningfully.

As luck would have it, the very same day my fellow jury was Susmita Das who casually asked me if I’d like to teach a module for her department! 

Cut to now- this semester, I was teaching Digital Design & Media to the third-year students at NIFT Mumbai, as a guest faculty in the Fashion Communication department.

It’s been one of the most grounding and fulfilling experiences of my career.
No travels, no distractions- just me, my students, and the joy of creating and learning together.

Honestly, it stretched me. It was outside my comfort zone. But it also reconnected me with something deep- my love for design education, and for witnessing growth unfold in real time.

This chapter has been unforgettable.

Sharing a few glimpses of the incredible student work that came out of it:
